Russian state scientists are alarmed by the mass death of bee colonies in the country, with uncontrolled pesticide use believed to be the cause.<img class="size-full wp-image-1267807 aligncenter" src="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bees.jpg?resize=640%2C337&#038;ssl=1" alt="" width="640" height="337" srcset="https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bees.jpg?w=1500&amp;ssl=1 1500w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bees.jpg?resize=300%2C158&amp;ssl=1 300w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bees.jpg?resize=768%2C404&amp;ssl=1 768w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bees.jpg?resize=1024%2C539&amp;ssl=1 1024w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bees.jpg?resize=58%2C31&amp;ssl=1 58w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bees.jpg?resize=260%2C137&amp;ssl=1 260w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bees.jpg?resize=200%2C105&amp;ssl=1 200w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bees.jpg?resize=560%2C295&amp;ssl=1 560w, https://i1.wp.com/cdn.vanguardngr.com/wp-content/uploads/2019/10/bees.jpg?w=1280&amp;ssl=1 1280w" sizes="(max-width: 640px) 100vw, 640px" data-recalc-dims="1" /> “The problem is that we do not produce our own pesticides,” Yelena Saltykova of the Russian state Institute of Biochemisty and Genetics said. “There are no strict controls here,” the official said. Putin proposes Russian missile defence for Saudi after oil attack(Opens in a new browser tab) The Russian government has noted that until the end of July more than 39,600 bee colonies, an estimated 1.5 per cent of all those in the country, have died. Saltykova believes the devastation could be much greater. “Unofficial statistics assume even higher numbers,” she said.(NAN) Vanguard Populations of bees, butterflies and other species important for 